%% Diagram: Decision tree — does an estimate justify caching, sharding, multi-region, or a CDN?
%% Type: flowchart
%%{init: {'htmlLabels': false}}%%
flowchart LR
    Start([Capacity<br/>estimate]) --> Q1{Peak QPS<br/>&gt; 10k?}
    Q1 -- "no" --> Q2{Egress &gt; 1 Gbps<br/>or global users?}
    Q1 -- "yes" --> Replicas[Add read replicas<br/>or stateless fleet]
    Replicas --> Q3{Write QPS &gt; 5k<br/>or DB &gt; 1 TB?}
    Q3 -- "no" --> Cache[Cache hot 20%<br/>target &gt;=80% hit rate]
    Q3 -- "yes" --> Shard[Shard by tenant<br/>or hash key]
    Cache --> Q2
    Shard --> Q2
    Q2 -- "no" --> Done([Single-region<br/>plan complete])
    Q2 -- "yes" --> CDN[Push static + media<br/>to CDN]
    CDN --> Q4{Global latency<br/>&lt; 100 ms?}
    Q4 -- "no" --> Done
    Q4 -- "yes" --> MultiRegion[Multi-region<br/>active-active]
    MultiRegion --> Done
